  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-09-10",
    "date": "2021-09-21T15:52:02Z",
    "text": "Closing the College Hunger Gap Act of 2021\n\nThis bill requires the Department of Education (ED) to collect data on the\u00a0food and housing insecurity of college students.\n\nSpecifically, ED must add questions that measure rates of food and housing insecurity to the National Postsecondary Student Aid Study. In addition, ED must collect\u00a0data on student eligibility under the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP).\n\nED must also provide students with contact information for the state agency that administers SNAP in their state."
  },
